page.title: 16FLORA IN HOLBERROW GREEN
page.content: The Feckenham Wylde Moor Nature Reserve is of greatest value for its flora and has many species of sedge and rush, in particular sea club-rush which is quite rare inland. Detailed investigations have taken place to record some 150 vascular plants, including the common spotted orchid, marsh arrow-grass, adders tongue fern, marsh roundwort, kemp agrimony, purple loosestrife. Other examples are Betony, Buttercup, Bindweed, Clover, Cowslip, Celery-leaved crowfoot, Chamomile, wild and scentless, Deadnettle, Fritillary, Herb Robert, Hedge Mustard, Hawksbeard/Nipplewort, Jack by the Hedge, Knap Weed, Medick, Oxslip, Old Men's Beard, Purple Scabious, Plantain, Pignot, Ribwort Plantain, Redveined dock, Self-Leaf, Scented May Weed, Thistle spear, Thistle ground, Vetch, Wild Rose.
